{{Quote|Chiss sages conclude that the Yuuzhan Vong must have spent generations traveling between galaxies. These invaders are not likely to consider the so-called Unknown Regions a daunting prospect.''"<br />"''I agree. The Chiss parliament does not, and neither do the Imperial leaders. The invasion path has swept steadily toward the Core Worlds, leading many to believe that the invaders will bypass both Chiss and Imperial territory entirely.''"<br />"''This phalanx has never been ruled by the thinking of tradition-bound Chiss senators, or by Imperial politicians whose first concern is personal power. Was a change-of-policy holocube issued during my recent absence?|Colonel Jagged Fel and Baron Soontir Fel debate the direction of the Yuuzhan Vong invasion|<ref name="DJ">''[[The New Jedi Order: Dark Journey]]''</ref>}}
The '''Chiss Senate''', also known as the '''Chiss parliament''' or simply the '''Parliament''', was a ruling legislative body of the [[Chiss Ascendancy/Legends|Chiss Ascendancy]] formed from at least twenty-eight colony [[Planet/Legends|worlds]] of the Ascendancy and presided by [[Senator/Legends|senators]]&mdash;[[House leader]]s who were [[Democracy/Legends|democratically]] elected by a colonial vote. Every [[Chiss/Legends|Chiss]] citizen, along with the four or more [[Ruling Families/Legends|Ruling Families]]&mdash;[[Csapla family|Csapla]], [[Nuruodo family|Nuruodo]], [[Inrokini family|Inrokini]], and [[Sabosen family|Sabosen]]&mdash;were also represented in the Senate. The Chiss Senate was headquartered in the [[House Palace]] in the [[City/Legends|city]] of [[Csaplar/Legends|Csaplar]], on the Ascendancy's [[Capital/Legends|capital]] world of [[Csilla/Legends|Csilla]].

==Description==
{{Quote|Parliament positions are democratically determined by colonial vote.|Sentientologist Tem Eliss, ''The University of Sanbra Guide to Intelligent Life''|<ref name="TC" />}}
[[File:ChissAscendancy.jpg|thumb|right|300px|Twenty-eight outlying Chiss colonies were represented in the Chiss Senate.]]
The Chiss Senate,<ref name="RSBF">{{GamerCite|7|Red Sky, Blue Flame}}</ref> also known as the Chiss parliament<ref name="DJ" /> or simply the Parliament,<ref name="TC" /> was a ruling<ref name="CSWE">{{CSWECite|I|154|Csaplar}}</ref> legislative body of the [[Chiss Ascendancy/Legends|Chiss Ascendancy]].<ref name="TC" /> [[Chiss/Legends|Chiss]] [[Senator/Legends|senators]]<ref name="DJ" />&mdash;[[House leader]]s who were [[Democracy/Legends|democratically]] elected by a colonial vote&mdash;represented at least twenty-eight colony [[Planet/Legends|worlds]] of the Ascendancy.<ref name="TC" /> Every Chiss citizen, along with the four [[Ruling Families/Legends|Ruling Families]]&mdash;[[Csapla family|Csapla]], [[Nuruodo family|Nuruodo]], [[Inrokini family|Inrokini]], and [[Sabosen family|Sabosen]]&mdash;also had representation in the Senate.<ref name="AA">''[[Alien Anthology]]''</ref> 

The Senate would make [[Local day/Legends|day]]-to-day decisions, while more complex issues would be deferred to the departmentalized [[Cabinet (Chiss)|Cabinet]], which in turn would pass important matters to the Ruling Families.<ref name="FF">{{FactFile|137|CHI 1-4|Chiss}}</ref> The Chiss Senate was headquartered in the [[House Palace]] in the [[City/Legends|city]] of [[Csaplar/Legends|Csaplar]], on the Ascendancy's [[Capital/Legends|capital]] world of [[Csilla/Legends|Csilla]].<ref name="TC" />

==History==
{{Quote|The heart of Chiss politics lies on Csilla, and in the four ruling families. At the House Palace in Csilla's capital city of Csaplar can be found the Cabinet and Parliament. The 28 outlying Chiss colonies are represented in the Parliament by appointed governors, or House leaders.|Sentientologist Tem Eliss, ''The University of Sanbra Guide to Intelligent Life''|<ref name="TC" />}}
[[File:Chiss_Ascendancy.svg|thumb|left|250px|Chiss senators of the Ascendancy (logo pictured) disagreed with Syndic Mitth'raw'nuruodo's Household Phalanx on the direction of Yuuzhan Vong invasion.]]
In [[19 ABY/Legends|19 ABY]],<ref name="Date">The events of ''[[Red Sky, Blue Flame]]'' take place in [[19 ABY/Legends|19 ABY]] according to ''[[The Essential Reader's Companion]]''.</ref> [[Commandant/Legends|Commandant]] [[Gimald Nuruodo]] of the [[Syndic Mitth'raw'nuruodo training academy]]<ref name="DJ" /> located on the [[Unknown Regions/Legends|Unknown Regions]] planet<ref name="RSBF" /> [[Rhigar/Legends|Rhigar]]<ref name="TEA">''[[The Essential Atlas]]''</ref> gave a formal nod to [[Empire of the Hand]] [[Commander/Legends|Commander]]<ref name="RSBF" /> [[Kres'ten'tarthi]], [[Core name/Legends|core name]] "Stent,"<ref name="SQ">''[[Survivor's Quest]]''</ref> that, according to [[Human/Legends|Human]] [[Cadet/Legends|cadet]] [[Jagged Fel]], was appropriate for the Chiss Senate.<ref name="RSBF" />

By [[25 ABY/Legends|25 ABY]],<ref name="Date 2">{{GamerCite|5|The University of Sanbra Guide to Intelligent Life: The Chiss}}, which is presented as an entry in [[in-universe]] [[The University of Sanbra Guide to Intelligent Life|guide]], mentions the [[Battle of Garqi]], which is depicted in ''[[The New Jedi Order: Dark Tide II: Ruin]]''. The events of ''Dark Tide II: Ruin'' take place in [[25 ABY/Legends|25 ABY]] according to ''[[The Essential Reader's Companion]]'', meaning the entry must have been written by that [[Standard year/Legends|year]].</ref> the Chiss Senate was described in ''[[The University of Sanbra Guide to Intelligent Life]]'', a [[Book/Legends|book]] published by the [[University of Sanbra]] and written by the [[sentientologist]] [[Tem Eliss]].<ref name="TC" /> In [[27 ABY/Legends|27 ABY]],<ref name="Date 3">The events of ''[[The New Jedi Order: Dark Journey]]'' take place in [[27 ABY/Legends|27 ABY]] according to ''[[The Essential Reader's Companion]]''.</ref> [[Baron of the Empire/Legends|Baron]] [[Soontir Fel/Legends|Soontir Fel]] of the Empire of the Hand, who was stationed at the secret [[Cherith base]] on an [[Unidentified inhospitable world|inhospitable world]], reminded his son, [[Colonel/Legends|Colonel]] Jagged Fel that the Chiss Senate did not agree with him on whether the [[Yuuzhan Vong]] [[Yuuzhan Vong War|invasion]] would affect the Chiss and Imperial territories in the Unknown Regions. In disbelief, Jagged derided the Chiss senators as "tradition-bound" and Imperial [[Politics/Legends|politicians]] as concerned with "personal power" and that [[Syndic/Legends|Syndic]] [[Mitth'raw'nuruodo/Legends|Mitth'raw'nuruodo's]] [[Syndic Mitth'raw'nuruodo's Household Phalanx|Household Phalanx]] was never aligned with their ideas.<ref name="DJ" />

==Behind the scenes==
[[File:The_Chiss_G5.jpg|thumb|300px|right|The Chiss Senate was introduced in the article "The University of Sanbra Guide to Intelligent Life: The Chiss".]]
The Chiss Senate was first mentioned as "Parliament" in the article "[[The University of Sanbra Guide to Intelligent Life: The Chiss]]," which was written by [[Juan Schwartz]] and published by [[Wizards of the Coast]] in the [[Star Wars Gamer 5|fifth issue]] of the ''[[Star Wars Gamer]]'' magazine<ref name="TC" /> on [[July 24]], [[2001]].<ref name="SW.com">{{SWArchive|url=gaming/other/rpg/news20010627.html|text=''Gamer'' #5. A Domain of Evil it is.}}</ref> It was first identified as the Chiss Senate in the short story "[[Red Sky, Blue Flame]]," written by [[Elaine Cunningham]] and published in the [[Star Wars Gamer 7|seventh issue]] of the ''Star Wars Gamer'' magazine<ref name="RSBF" /> on [[October 16]], 2001,<ref name="Rd">{{SWArchive|url=gaming/other/rpg/news20011018.html|text=Live on the Fringe: ''Gamer'' # 7}}</ref> and was identified as the Chiss parliament in the [[2002]] novel ''[[The New Jedi Order: Dark Journey]]'', also written by Cunningham.<ref name="DJ" />

